;
BIOMOLECULE: 1
THIS ENTRY CONTAINS THE CRYSTALLOGRAPHIC ASYMMETRIC UNIT
WHICH CONSISTS OF 1 CHAIN. SEE REMARK 350 FOR
INFORMATION ON GENERATING THE BIOLOGICAL MOLECULE.
THE BIOLOGICAL UNIT IS A DIMER FORMED BY DISULFIDE BOND
BETWEEN CYSTEINES 44. THE DISULFIDE BOND OVERLAPS WITH
THE CRYSTALLOGRAPHIC 2-FOLD AXIS. THE DIMER IS A
SYMMETRICAL DIMER.
;
